<h2 id="physics-highlights">Physics Highlights</h2>

<div class="row">

  <div class="col-sm-6 clearfix">
    <div class="well">
      <pubtit>Lightweight self-conjugate nucleus <sup>80</sup>Zr</pubtit>
      <p><img src="http://localhost:4000/images/highlightpic/80Zr_fig.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>This work provides evidence for the existence of a deformed double shell closure in <sup>80</sup>Zr  through high precision Penning trap mass measurements of <span style="white-space: nowrap"><sup>80-83</sup>Zr</span>. A statistical Bayesian model mixing analysis is used to interpret an observed mass anomaly.
</p>
      <p><b>Contact: </b><em>Witek Nazarewicz (<a href="mailto:witek@frib.msu.edu">witek@frib.msu.edu</a>)</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="http://localhost:4000/highlights/80Zr.pdf" target="_blank">Click for one-page pdf highlight slide</a></strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

